usage/DEPLOYMENT.html.title: Deployment
usage/DEPLOYMENT.html.body:
Deployment
Download the deployment package
You can download the deployment package from web page or command line.

From web:Go to the release page of this project. Select the package according to the architecture of your machine.

From command line:  
wget https://github.com/[OWNER]/[REPO]/releases/download/[VERSION]/[REPO]-[ARCH]-[VERSION].zip


VERSION : the release tag  
ARCH : the architecture of your machine 

e.g : Deploy a [REPO] on a x86 machine with the release 0.5.6 by executing
wget https://github.com/[OWNER]/[REPO]/releases/download/0.5.6/[REPO]-x86-0.5.6.zip



Unzip
unzip [REPO]-[ARCH]-[VERSION].zip
cd [REPO]-imageAPI-[ARCH]

Generate the docker compose file
Docker compose file is used for [REPO] deployment. Its generation requires three parameters:

[VARIABLE] : EXPLAINATION.  

make config

e.g : Generate a compose file named [NAME].yml .
cd ~/[REPO]-x86/
make config 
Therefore a compose file named `[NAME].yml` is generated in `~/[REPO]-imageAPI-x86/compose/`.
```yaml
# [NAME].yml
Start the service
Start the service with the name you specified in the config step above.
make start NAME=[COMP_NAME]

e.g: start service [NAME]
cd [REPO]-imageAPI-x86/
make start NAME=[NAME]

After starting the service successfully, you may see the output similar with the following: 
docker-compose -p [NAME] -f ~/[REPO]-imageAPI-x86/compose/[NAME].yml up -d
Restart the service
make restart NAME=[COMP_NAME]

e.g
make restart NAME=[NAME]

After restarting the service successfully, you may see the output similar with the following:
docker-compose -p [NAME] -f ~/[REPO]-imageAPI-x86/compose/[NAME].yml up -d --force-recreate
Check status of the service
make status NAME=[COMP_NAME]

e.g,
make stop NAME=[NAME]

You may see the output similar with the following:
docker-compose -p [NAME] -f ~/[REPO]-imageAPI-x86/compose/[NAME].yml ps
docker-compose -p [NAME] -f ~/[REPO]-imageAPI-x86/compose/[NAME].yml logs
Stop the service
make stop NAME=[COMP_NAME]

e.g,
make stop NAME=[NAME]

After stoping the service successfully, you may see the output similar with the following:
docker-compose -p [NAME] -f ~/[REPO]-imageAPI-x86/compose/[NAME].yml down
List the services
make list

You may see the output similar with the following:
for compose in `ls ~/[REPO]-imageAPI-x86/compose`;do name=`echo $compose|awk -F "." '{print $1}'`;echo $name;docker-compose -p $name -f ~/[REPO]-imageAPI-x86/compose/$compose ps;done
[NAME]
Name   Command   State   Ports
------------------------------
...
Remove the compose file
make remove NAME=[COMP_NAME]

e.g,
make remove NAME=[NAME]

You may see the output similar with the following:
rm ~/[REPO]-imageAPI-x86/compose/[NAME].yml
Check whether the remove step successfully:
ls compose | grep [NAME]

usage/usermanual/INFO.html.title: info
usage/usermanual/INFO.html.body:
info
info is used to customize user configuration of services. Users can modify it to meet their own requirements. 
info template
dnsmasq: 
  dhcp-range: 192.168.0.5,192.168.0.150,12h
  dhcp-option: 6,192.168.0.1
  cache-size: 3000
  domain: powter
  local: /powter
  dns-server:
    - ip: 1.1.1.1
      ports:
        start-port: 16350
        end-port: 16370
    - ip: 2.2.2.2
      ports:
        start-port: 16350
        end-port: 16370
bypass:
  config:
    lan: br0
    base_port: 2010
    number: 16  
  white:
    - filename: 03-vps
      content:
      - ip/net
      - ip/net
    - filename: 04-test
      content:
      - ip/net
      - ip/net
sskcp:
  - mode: sskcp/ss
    logdir: ~/snmplog 
    listenport: 2001
    vpsip: 
    vpsport: 
    key:
    dest: ~/conf

info is yaml file and you can test whether it is ok after modification with:
cd powter-client
make test_info INFO=path/to/info
Detailed info about how to modify info of dnsmasq, bypass, sskcp

usage/usermanual/INSTALL.html.title: Install
usage/usermanual/INSTALL.html.body:
Install
Download powter-client
wget  https://github.com/hilanderas/powter-client/releases/download/version/powter-client-m.n.p.zip

Download images, congenerator, images API for 3 projects
make prepare

Test whether download resources successfully
make test_prepare

Generate configuration

Provide info file, you will be asked to edit it on line, just enter :wq to save the file if you don't need to modify it.
make config INFO=path/to/info

Please note that if info is not provided, a default one will pop up and you can edit it on line before save.
make config


If you want script keep running without stopping, add INTRERACTION=false at the end of the command
make config INFO=path/to/info INTRERACTION=false



Test configuration generated
make test_config

Start services
make start

usage/usermanual/UNINSTALL.html.title: Uninstall
usage/usermanual/UNINSTALL.html.body:
Uninstall
Uninstall the services
Delete all services, default info, compose configuration  
cd powter-client
make uninstall
Delete downloads

Delete all resource downloaded in prepare session, including docker images, confgenerator and image API packages
make remove


Test whether removal is successful
make test_remove

usage/usermanual/UPDATEDNS.html.title: Update dns
usage/usermanual/UPDATEDNS.html.body:
Replace dns server
Sometimes vps used as dns server is in low performance or high latency, so you want to replace it to a new one. 
There are 2 ways to do this:

Update info on line
Update info with file provided by user

Modify info on line

Modify  ip in dns-server and save
make config


Restart dns service
make restart_dns


Check status
make status_dns



Modify info file

Modify  ip in dns-server in info file and savevi /path/to/info


Generate configuration
make config INFO=/path/to/info INTERATION=no


Restart dns service
make restart_dns


Check status
make status_dns
